<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-119-119 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 913 358</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Sources  July 1991 v2 n7 p57(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM shoots for the stars. (Forum) (Hollywood presentationsoftware) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pepper, Jon.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   Hollywood (Presentation software) (Product introduction)Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionPresentation Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IBM is best known as a vendor of PC hardware.andP;  But the company's desktopsoftware division (Milford, CT, 800-426-7699) is trying to change that.andP;  IBMCurrent, its Windows-based personal information manager, received goodreviews when it was introduced last year.andP;  Now IBM is setting its sights evenhigher with Hollywood, a full-featured presentation graphics program thatruns under Microsoft Windows.andM;Hollywood is targeted at the heart of the presentation graphics market,competing with products like Microsoft PowerPoint, Micrografx Charisma, LotusFreelance Plus, and Harvard Graphics.andP;  A look at a beta copy showed thatHollywood not only provides powerful features, including robust drawing toolslike bezier curves and stacked objects, but also is easy to learn and use.andO;Hollywood's interface provides a predefined selection of fonts and color soinexperienced users or non-artists can easily create sophisticated charts andgraphs.andP;  The program includes an outliner and spell-checker.andM;To provide high-qaulity screen and output capabilities, Hollywoodincorporates the Speedo font-scaling technology from Bitstream.andP;  TheBitstream fonts provide true WYSIWYG capability for Hollywood charts, graphs,and text charts.andP;  The extensive feature list includes the ability to producescreen shows, speaker notes, and thumbnail sketches; and to mirror, rotate,and stretch text.andM;At press time, Hollywood was scheduled to be shipped at the end of May with alist price of $495; it should cost about $325 by mail.andO;</TEXT></DOC>